- The summits of Volcanic Hills when<lb/>
elevated to any considerable height, or after<lb/>
having felt the effects of an Eruption present<lb/>
a striking contrast when examined in the<lb/>
same view with the lower regions -<lb/>
Black &amp; rugged &amp; barren; if not<lb/>
covered with snow, they bear the<lb/>
evidences of having been changed<lb/>
by the force of fire. -<lb/>
Formed of Lava &amp; strewed over<lb/>
with <rs xml:id="ttag51" ref="#chemical_482" type="chemical">
