irregular in its forms &amp; various<lb/>
in its constitution. - <lb/>
Brislac thus describes the Crater of<lb/>
Vesuvius as it appeared in 1800 -<lb/>
"The Cone" he says, "is cut in an inclined<lb/>
plane, having its direction from North<lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <pb n="10" xml:id="pb-10" facs="#i10"/>
                  <lb/>
