itself arise volumes of this smoke,<lb/>
which darken the face of heaven &amp; the<lb/>
colour of which is constantly varying.<lb/>
The sun seen through this smoke, sometimes<lb/>
appears perfectly white, &amp; sometimes of a<lb/>
blood red colour. We looked with<lb/>
long &amp; anxious expectancy, for a<lb/>
                  <lb/>
