Of a Mind which promised much for<lb/>
the Philosophy of this Subject; but<lb/>
death cut off this bloom of promise<lb/>
&amp; hope for the Scientific World at<lb/>
the moment it was brightest. -<lb/>
No person attached to truth can<lb/>
read his paper without a feeling<lb/>
of regret, &amp; I hope I may be<lb/>
excused for the strong expression<lb/>
of this regret, for whilst I admired him<lb/>
as a Philosopher, I loved him as a<lb/>
